	Great place	With the exception of the &quot;free breakfast&quot; which is really a sales presentation, this is a great property. I would highly recommend if you are a 2nd or 3rd timer Vegas vacationer and you are a little tired of the strip. This is a great place to bring a family. I would recommend renting a car for your strip/show visits. We found a garage on the strip (near the M&amp;M store) where we could park for $3.00 all day. There was a full kitchen so not all of your time has to be spent looking for places to eat. This property is very close to a Whole Foods and Wal-mart. Parking can be challenging if you are coming in late from a show. Very close to M Casino down the road if you want to gamble but don't want to deal with the strip. I recommend Red Cup cafe for all 3 of your meals. Portions are generous. You can bring your leftovers and put them in the full size refridgerator that is available. I will stay again!	
