Oct 3 2007 	Loved the Grandview at Las Vegas! Very roomy and with a full kitchen no less.	We spent 3 nights at the Grandview at Las Vegas, and our accommodation was excellent....we had a 1 bedroom with a full kitchen. Across the courtyard was the fitness center and swimming pools and spas. The only negative I saw was the pool was too cool to really enjoy....the weather was warm, mid 80's, but when you got into the pool, it was cold. Perhaps the heat could be turned up a few degrees so you can float and enjoy the water. Maybe next time it will be warmer. The South Pointe casino/hotel is next door, and the Coronado Cafe has very reasonable prices, and the food was very delicious. We ate there for all our meals. Inside are 6 restaurants, so there is something for everyone there. Grandview does not have any restaurants on site, so you need to have a car to really go anywhere besides South Pointe. We walked at least 1 mile before we got to a bus stop, but we were able to take the Trolley to the strip for $4.25 for a 6 hour pass. I loved that the refrigerator had its own ice maker. Though we did not eat in the unit, we basically wanted to stay at this resort as we are an every other year owner of 1 week now, and having spent time there, we will now know what to bring when we come and stay for a week.	
