 - just call and they'll be there. We requested a rental and were told it would be there at 10:00 AM. Well, they forgot to call, so at 11:00, someone was there to pick us up to take us to a rental place. We got back with the car at 3:00 PM - totally wasting half a day. Rent one from the airport and all will be fine!The people at the front desk didn't even know about restaurants in the next casino or where a grocery store was. FYI - there is a 7-11 and some other little grocery store about 1 mile north, &amp; a larger one further north &amp; only one restaurant is open next door late. The buffet there was fabulous though (the Southpoint Casino) - so much to choose from &amp; cheaper than those on the strip.If you stay at the Grandview - it is nice and they certainly leave you alone because there is no service there, but be prepared with your own transportation. And make sure your entry cards are given correct access the first time!	
